fn ->
  try do
    task_loaded = Code.ensure_loaded(Mix.Task)
    mix_compile(task_loaded, compilers, apps, args, state.timestamp(), purge_fallback?)
  catch
    :exit, {:shutdown, 1} ->
      :error

    kind, reason ->
      IO.puts(Exception.format(kind, reason, __STACKTRACE__))
      :error
  end
end

fn ->
  purge_fallback? =
    case Phoenix.CodeReloader.MixListener.started?() do
      x when :erlang.orelse(:erlang."=:="(x, false), :erlang."=:="(x, nil)) ->
        warn_missing_mix_listener()
        true

      _ ->
        Phoenix.CodeReloader.MixListener.purge(apps)
        false
    end

  backup = load_backup(endpoint)

  {res, out} =
    proxy_io(fn ->
      try do
        task_loaded = Code.ensure_loaded(Mix.Task)
        mix_compile(task_loaded, compilers, apps, args, state.timestamp(), purge_fallback?)
      catch
        :exit, {:shutdown, 1} ->
          :error

        kind, reason ->
          IO.puts(Exception.format(kind, reason, __STACKTRACE__))
          :error
      end
    end)

  {backup, res, out}
end

    case Keyword.get(opts, :check_origin, endpoint.config(:check_origin)) do
      origins when :erlang.is_list(origins) ->
        Enum.map(origins, &parse_origin/1)

      boolean when :erlang.is_boolean(boolean) ->

      {module, function, arguments} ->
        {module, function, arguments}

      :conn ->
        :conn

      invalid ->
        :erlang.error(
          ArgumentError.exception(
            <<":check_origin expects a boolean, list of hosts, :conn, or MFA tuple, got: "::binary,
              Kernel.inspect(invalid)::binary>>

  {:cache, check_origin}
